Trim the @courgette{1} then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Bring a large #saucepan of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{a drizzle} in a #frying pan on medium-high heat and add the courgette. Fry until starting to soften, ~{5-6%mins}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then remove the courgette to a #bowl and set aside. Add a little more @olive oil{a little more} to the now empty frying pan and pop back on medium-high heat. Add the @British pork and oregano sausage meat{225%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Break it up with a #spoon as it cooks.

When the sausage meat has browned, return the courgette to the frying pan. Add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1} and @chicken stock powder{1} along with a @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some). Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Stir together, bring to the boil then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{10-12%mins}.

While the sauce is cooking, add the @linguine{200%g} to your saucepan of boiling water. Cook for ~{12%mins}.

> Tip! Add a splash of the pasta water to the sauce if it starts to look too thick!

When the pasta is cooked, drain it in a #colander. Add the drained pasta to the frying pan with the sauce and toss or stir together.

If you like a bit of heat, add @?red chilli flakes{pinch} to the pasta before serving.

> Careful - the chilli flakes are hot!

Sprinkle over the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated). Enjoy!